-- South Africa Says Posts Monthly Budget Surplus of $1.22 Billion in June
-- Vernon Wessels
-- 2010-07-30T12:06:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/south-africa-says-posts-monthly-budget-surplus-of-1-22-billion-in-june.html

          
          
             South Africa posted a budget surplus
of 8.93 billion rand in June from a year-earlier deficit of
477.32 million rand, the National Treasury said.  
 Government revenue rose to 74.65 billion rand in June from
65.57 billion rand in the same month a year ago, the Pretoria-
based government department said on its website today.
Expenditure amounted to 65.73 billion rand from 66.05 billion
rand a year earlier, it said.  
          
          


  


        